Germany's New Warship Delayed Again
Germany’s newest naval frigate was supposed to be commissioned in 2014 to replace aging Cold War warships, but that won’t happen until next year because of faulty systems and rising costs, local media reported.
The entry into service of the Rheinland-Pfalz, the flagship of the new Baden-Wuerttemberg frigate class, has now been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit, which quotes a military spokesman.
The vessel was supposed to be introduced to the maritime forces in 2014, but problems arising after delivery have affected this ambitious project.
The four Baden-Wuerttemberg-class ships that the Navy ordered in 2007 will replace the old Bremen-class frigates.
